<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Would stun attacks stop him?</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Gray Rage (DB)">Gray Rage (DB)</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 9:31 a.m. 6/6/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Would stun attacks stop him?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=2141" TARGET=_self>Bards, are they the uber-class of PvP?</A> (TheBlack)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>The only way to be beat a healer is if u can keep him stunned long enough NOT to be able to heal. Maybe the same would work with the bard. But, to be honest, I have also heard that Bards are virtually unkillable and to be even more honest, I should not be voicing any opinion on this at all as I don't know squat about them....*grins*.

<P>I have faith, however, that everyone else does and Verant will eventually fix it and make all Classes a bit more equal.
<P>I STILL WISH THEY WOULD PUT IN A REAL AUTOATTAACK FEATURE FOR WARRIOR TYPES WHICH WILL ALLOW THEM TO AUTO FOLLOW THEIR FOE! Losing your oponant to lag really sucks I would imagine.
<P>Gray
<P>&gt; In reading some of the more recent posts I got the impression
<BR>&gt; that Bards may have emerged as the uber-class on the PvP server.
<BR>&gt; Is this true? If so, how should Bard's be tuned so they are more
<BR>&gt; on par with other classes in the 1 on 1 PvP situations?
<P>&gt; For example, how does one counter a spirited up bard who is
<BR>&gt; tossing around direct damage spells that require no mana?
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
